SIMPLE: nuclear
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Nuclear
<hw>Nu"cle*ar</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>,
}</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Of or pertaining to a nucleus;
<as>as, the <ex>nuclear</ex> spindle (see <xex>Illust.</xex> of
<er>Karyokinesis</er>) or the <ex>nuclear</ex> fibrils of a cell; the
<ex>nuclear</ex> part of a comet, etc.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nuclear</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Nuclear
<hw>Nu"cle*ar</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>of,
pertaining to, or using <er>nuclear weapons</er>; <as>a <ex>nuclear</ex>
exchange, i.e. a reciprocal bombardment by nuclear
weapons.</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Of, pertaining to, or powered by atomic energy; same
as <er>nuclear-powered</er>; <as>as, a <ex>nuclear</ex> submarine; a
<ex>nuclear</ex> power plant</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Of or pertaining to nations possessing nuclear
weapons; <as>as, the <ex>nuclear</ex> club</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nuclear device</ent>⟦br⟧
